org.apache.flex.compiler.problems

Class OperandStackUnderflowProblem

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.problems.CompilerProblem
      • org.apache.flex.compiler.problems.InvalidByteCodeGeneratedProblem
        • org.apache.flex.compiler.problems.OperandStackUnderflowProblem
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISourceLocation, ICompilerProblem

    public final class OperandStackUnderflowProblem
extends InvalidByteCodeGeneratedProblem
    Internal compiler problem created when the code generator produces code in a method body that underflows the operand stack.

    This compiler problem is created when AET, detects a operand stack underflow in MethodBodyInfo.computeFrameCounts(IDiagnosticsVisitor).
